<div class="project-text">
    <h3>The Project</h3>
    <p>Some of the most satisfying work comes from the smallest briefs, and this is the one I think of first. Six hours before the event, everything was ready except the presentation. My task was to build something credible from a single text file with no visual direction whatsoever.</p>
    <p>One key visual, the rounded X, and one concept: the path. I used the X at different sizes and positions to suggest direction and movement. For section titles I gave the X a specific visual meaning each time. In "data and evidence" I placed many faint X shapes with only one visible, to point to exactly that: an evidence. Same logic carried through every other section.</p>
    <p>For the event identity I had to invent from scratch too. My thought was that innovation requires action and decisions, so I split the Italian word in two: innov AZIONE. Six hours later the client was happy with something they had not expected beyond a cleaned-up PowerPoint.</p>
